   For the longest of tymes i have been searching for a guild such as this. I love it! The idea, it's great to help others.<br>
   Ever since i purchased EverQuest i had been playing on the Xegony server. HAving had around 20 different characters i finally stoped changing and decided to keep my Shaman barbarian for many reasons. I had never leveled passed 11 for one good reason, I would always find myself Role Playing and decide to buff someone with everyhting i had, help out a newbie, or give away 5 longsaxe's to the first 5 people to poke me at a gate as i have done before.<br>
   I really didnt care much for leveling when i felt the graciousness and warmhearted feeling of making a new friend from giving them something or helping them greatly. But then tragedy struct my character.<br>
   I had noticed that mnay higher level Shamans had much better stats than I. When I told them my stats they often told me i need to start a new Shaman becuase being a level 11 Shaman with only 92 wisdom isnt the greatest. So i contacted my friends sadly to hear none of them could come to my aid to transport my stuff to my new charcter. So i left the armor, the money, the wepons all at the bottom of well. But when i came back it was all gone.<br>
           (almost over just hang on)<br>
   Since it had taken me so long to achieve all of that stuff and it had all been lost, i saw no need to still use that Shaman or the server since apparently the people there cared no less for friends or other characters as they did goind to school. I could find no GM t help me, no other player to lend me some items, and no friend to back me up. Sad since i had helped so many and got so little help.<br>
   I then Began looking for a new server to play on, one with generous people and many newbies to help out when needs be. Then I here of this clan on a reletivley new server with apparently many newbies and generous people to probably back me up when hard tymes strike others.<br>
   I would really love to join your clan, though i dont have a character yet on this server i plan to make a Barbarian Shaman named Sallof Spiritstrike. If one of you would reply to this &quot;long&quot; post and tell me whom to contact and when i would be so gratefull.<br>
   Thankyou for reading this &quot;long&quot; post but for some reason felt a need to to write why i want to join the clan, how nice i am, and a little background on myself while playing this social, rat killing, role playing game we all call EverQuest.<br>
   <br>
So as i often to say to players after lending them a hand or having one lent to me:   <br>
       May The God's Smile Upon You Friend,<br>
<br>
Sallof Spiritstrike<br>
Barbarian Shaman<br>
   <br>
