<br>
I am so glad you found us! We will be most honored to be<br>
your companions on this happy pilgrimage through Norrath!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I was saddened to hear of the terrible things that happened<br>
to you. It is terrible when people who are suppossed to be<br>
your friends mistreat you so badly. I have had similiar things<br>
happen and then I withdrew and suspected everyone. It's not a<br>
good place to be in.<br>
<br>
One thing I try to remember is that even good people can<br>
disappoint you because no one is perfect and we all have good<br>
and bad moments. So although I believe that all of us in this<br>
guild have good intentions, it is inevitable that we will all let<br>
each other down at times. Let's try to forgive each other and<br>
go on please when that happens...I will probably need a lot<br>
of forgiveness and tolerance from everyone.<br>
<br>
But I can promise you that if you ever need someone trustworthy<br>
to help you trade your stuff, either I or Fyrewurkz will be glad to<br>
help you, as I am sure many others in the guild will too. Before<br>
this, Fyre and I were on another server and in a huge guild. He<br>
asked someone in the guild to help him trade his stuff. He gave<br>
the guy his stuff and 50 plat...and the guy said he never got the<br>
50 plat from him. There is no way of telling what happened, but<br>
it looks like the guy took the 50 plat from Fyre. That didn't feel good.<br>
<br>
It's the goal of this guild to practice acts of kindness...not just for<br>
people outside the guild, but for inside the guild too. Kindness<br>
begins at home. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Ok...I will get off my soapbox now and go to bed everyone!  :LOL<br>
<br>
Sallof, I will look for you in the game so I can invite you into the guild.<br>
<br>
Good Journey,<br>
Hamadryad Long<br>
<br>
PS Yes when you make your shaman, please put everything you<br>
can into wisdom.<br>
